about.summary: Significance tests for canonical correlation analysis, including asymptotic tests and a Monte Carlo method

name: r-ccp
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '1.1' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-ccp
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/CCP_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/CCP/CCP_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 9d21cda05221f1a458fe2938cd5ff0e89711ef058865d25f9894a275c7805d1e

build:
  noarch: generic
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1001
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:

  host:
    - r-base
  run:
    - r-base

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('CCP')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('CCP')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=CCP
  license: GPL
  summary: Significance tests for canonical correlation analysis, including asymptotic tests
    and a Monte Carlo method
  license_family: GPL
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
